The '''''1974 American 500''''' was a [[NASCAR]] [[Sprint Cup Series|Winston Cup Series]] racing event that was held on October 20, 1974 at [[Rockingham Speedway|North Carolina Motor Speedway]] in [[Rockingham, North Carolina|Rockingham]], [[North Carolina]].

[[Joe Millikan]] would make his NASCAR Cup Series debut while [[Jerry Schild]] would exit the series in this event. A rare NASCAR Winston Cup appearance by former [[Champ Car]] team owner and driver [[Tony Bettenhausen, Jr.]] would make this race into a landmark event in motorsports history. His first NASCAR appearance was at the [[1973 Atlanta 500]] while his final appearance at the Cup Series level would be at the [[1982 Champion Spark Plug 400]].

==Summary==
There were 36 drivers who competed in this 492-lap racing event. All except for [[Canada|Canadian]] native [[Earl Ross]] were born and bred in the [[United States|United States of America]]. [[Joe Frasson]]'s difficulties in handling his steering problems on lap 4 caused him to be credited with the last-place finish for this event. [[Elmo Langley]] became the lowest-finishing driver to finish the event; while [[J.D. McDuffie]] would be the last driver to achieve a DNF due to troubles with his stock car engine on lap 447. The model years of the vehicles ranged from 1972 to 1974; with most of the field driving [[Chevrolet]] and [[Dodge]] vehicles.<ref name="rr">[http://www.racing-reference.info/race/1974_American_500/W ''1974 American 500''] racing information at Racing Reference</ref>

After four hours and thirteen minutes of racing, [[David Pearson (racing driver)|David Pearson]] would defeat [[Cale Yarborough]] by slightly more than two seconds in front of an eager audience of 35,000 NASCAR followers. While [[Richard Petty]], [[Buddy Baker]] and David Pearson would dominate the opening laps of this event, the final laps would become a "Cale Yarborough and David Pearson show." The average speed of the vehicles in this racing event was {{convert|118.493|mph|km/h}} while Richard Petty would metaphorically scorch the track with his solo qualifying speed of {{convert|135.297|mph|km/h}}.<ref name="rr"/>

Individual earnings for each driver ranged for the winner's share of $16,350 (${{formatnum:{{Inflation|US|16350|1974|r=2}}}} in today's money) to the last-place finisher's share of $550 (${{formatnum:{{Inflation|US|550|1974|r=2}}}} in today's money). NASCAR officials permitted the handover of $99,465 for all the qualifying drivers of this racing event (${{formatnum:{{Inflation|US|99465|1974|r=2}}}} in today's money).<ref>[http://fantasyracingcheatsheet.com/nascar/races/results/1974/north-carolina-speedway/american-500/1347 Prize winnings information for the ''1974 American 500''] at Fantasy Racing Cheat Sheet</ref>

